    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://losangeles.craigslist.org/lgb/sec/6044017873.html"></div>
        </div>
Armored Protective Services, Inc. is currently in search of Armed Security Guards, Full-Time /Part time  are available  around the Long Beach area, only a few shifts left. <br>
<br>
Apply today= work tomorrow. <br>
<br>
Role and Responsibilities:<br>
-Patrol facility or man post as instructed and serve as a general security presence and visible deterrent to crime and client rule infractions. <br>
-Detect suspicious activities and watch for criminal acts or client rule infractions at or near assigned post which may be a threat to --the property, client or employees at the site. <br>
-Report all incidents, accidents or medical emergencies. <br>
-Respond to emergencies, such as medical and bomb threats; and to alarms, such as fire and intrusion by following emergency response proceedings. <br>
-Comes to work; is on time and completes shift assignments (including overtime, if assigned). <br>
-Has a neat, professional appearance and comes to work in complete and clean assigned.<br>
-Has a friendly professional demeanor and provides quality customer service.<br>
-Is a good communicator (both verbal and written) and is capable of handling typical crisis situations both efficiently and effectively. <br>
-Understands successfully executes his/her post orders including enforcement of client and company policies, rules and regulations. <br>
<br>
Qualifications and Education Requirements:<br>
-Must have a high school diploma or GED. At least 2 years work history.<br>
-Ability to communicate effectively both orally and in writing for the purpose of public interaction and report writing.<br>
-Authorized to work in the United States.<br>
-Ability to perform essential functions of the position with or without reasonable accommodation.<br>
-Willing to participate in Armored Protective services, pre-employment process which may include drug testing and full background investigation.<br>
-Ability to maintain satisfactory attendance and punctuality standard.<br>
-Neat and professional appearance.<br>
-Friendly and professional demeanor.<br>
-Ability to provide quality customer service.<br>
-Ability to handle typical and crisis situations efficiently and effectively at client site.<br>
<br>
<br>
***Please reply to this job posting with a copy of your resume.<br>
Email resumes to: ARMOREDPROTECTIVESVC@GMAIL.COM<br>
And call our JOB LINE at (866)752-6948 EXT 2 <br>
<br>
<br>
Pay rate is set by post:<br>
<br>
-Entry Armed Guards 13.00 - 14.00/ Unarmed Guards 10.25 - 11.00<br>
<br>
<br>
Principals only. Recruiters, please don't contact this job poster.<br>
do NOT contact us with unsolicited services or offers<br>
    </section>

